{"id":11113,"date":"2022-02-10T12:53:55","date_gmt":"2022-02-10T10:53:55","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/?p=11113"},"modified":"2022-02-10T12:53:55","modified_gmt":"2022-02-10T10:53:55","slug":"speaker-wants-public-education-on-constitution-09-02-2022","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/speaker-wants-public-education-on-constitution-09-02-2022\/","title":{"rendered":"Speaker wants public education on Constitution, 09\/02\/2022"},"content":{"rendered":"<div id=\"attachment_11114\" style=\"width: 310px\" class=\"wp-caption alignleft\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-11114\" class=\"size-medium wp-image-11114\" src=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/Constitution-2-300x113.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"113\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/Constitution-2-300x113.jpg 300w, https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/Constitution-2-1024x384.jpg 1024w, https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/Constitution-2-768x288.jpg 768w, https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/Constitution-2-1536x576.jpg 1536w, https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/Constitution-2.jpg 1600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" \/><p id=\"caption-attachment-11114\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Hon. Prof. Peter Katjavivi reflecting on the drafting and adoption of the Constitution during an interview to commemorate the 32nd anniversary of its adoption. The interview took place in the Constitution room where the Constituent Assembly sat to draft the Constitution over 30 years ago.<\/p><\/div>\n<p>Story by George Sanzila<\/p>\n<p>Windhoek &#8211; The Speaker of the National Assembly, Hon. Prof. Peter Katjavivi has suggested that civic education be held to inform and educate Namibian citizens about the purpose and importance of the constitution.<\/p>\n<p>Hon. Katjavivi said this in an interview with the media on Wednesday, (09\/02\/2022) during the marking of the 32nd anniversary of the adoption of the Namibian Constitution.<\/p>\n<p>According to the Speaker, targeted civic education on the Constitution has the potential to enhance knowledge on Namibia\u2019s supreme law as well as the democratic processes.<\/p>\n<p>\u201cI would like to see targeted civics education in schools and in the media. This should not be a once off event but should be a continuous exercise carried out across the country. It would build an understanding of the Constitution and a knowledge of democratic processes,\u201d said Katjavivi.<\/p>\n<p>The Speaker further noted that the Constitution adopted over 30 years ago provides a framework under which all legislation operates.<br \/>\nHe urged Namibians to emulate the example set by the Constituent Assembly that had worked tirelessly together leading to the adoption of the constitution by consensus for the common good.<\/p>\n<p>\u201cThose of us who were part of the Constituent Assembly, remember this as a unique process that was carried out with utmost commitment and dedication. There were challenges but they were overcome under the careful handling of the process by the Chairperson of the drafting committee, our current President H.E. Hage Geingob,\u201d remembered Hon. Katjavivi.<br \/>\n\u201cThe drafting produced an understanding of the need to work together for the common good of the country. That is what led to the adoption of the Constitution by consensus,\u201d he added.<\/p>\n<p>Hon. Katjavivi noted that the Constitution has culminated into the adoption of many progressive legislations since independence. He further lauded the proposed legislations (Bills) that are scheduled to be tabled when National Assembly resumes business on Tuesday (15\/02\/2022).<br \/>\n\u201cWe have already adopted many laws since 1990 that have built upon the Constitution and further defined how we want our society to grow and operate. I can say with confidence that the current list of legislation due to be tabled in the National Assembly during this session does speak to the needs and aspirations of the people of Namibia,\u201d said the Speaker.<\/p>\n<p>The drafting committee of the Constituent Assembly represented political parties that had just participated in the first free and fair elections held in November 1989, and was tasked to write Namibia\u2019s Constitution. Namibia\u2019s current President, Hage Geingob was Chairman of the committee. The Constitution came into force on 21 March 1990 when Namibia became independent.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Story by George Sanzila Windhoek &#8211; The Speaker of the National Assembly, Hon. Prof. Peter Katjavivi has suggested that civic education be held to inform and educate Namibian citizens about the purpose and importance of the constitution. Hon. Katjavivi said this in an interview with the media on Wednesday, (09\/02\/2022) during the marking of the&hellip;<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":17,"featured_media":11114,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":[],"categories":[159,39],"tags":[],"class_list":["post-11113","post","type-post","status-publish","format-standard","has-post-thumbnail","hentry","category-home-page-slider","category-news","category-159","category-39","description-off"],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/11113","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/17"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=11113"}],"version-history":[{"count":2,"href":"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/po